The paper introduces a new data structure for approximate set membership, which is a topic in computer science that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The example application given is in packet processing, which suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses false positives and their impact on performance, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper presents simulations using both synthetic data sets and real packet traces, which suggests a focus on system performance and optimization (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
